# UNIT App — Cursor Context

## What This App Is
Delivery driver tool for Speed X drivers. Scan packages → assign to geographic zones
→ optimize route → sequential numbered navigation. Built for Director X's daily routes.
Director X drives a 2018 Jeep Grand Cherokee (suv_midsize).

## Live URL
https://unit-6gxn.onrender.com

## Stack
- Backend: Python / Flask
- Database: SQLite
- AI Vision: Anthropic Claude Vision (package scanning / address extraction)
- Routing: OSRM
- Maps: Leaflet.js
- Frontend: HTML/CSS/JS (served via Flask templates)

## Project Structure
- app.py — main Flask app, all routes and logic
- templates/ — HTML templates (scan, map, route views)
- static/ — CSS, JS, assets
- database.db — SQLite (packages, addresses, routes, zone intel)
- start.sh — local run script

## Vehicle Zones (Jeep Grand Cherokee — suv_midsize)
Load order (deepest first):
1. Cargo Back — furthest deliveries, loaded first
2. Cargo Middle
3. Cargo Liftgate
4. Back Seat R / M / L
5. Front Passenger — closest deliveries, loaded last

## Current Architecture (Being Rebuilt)
### What exists:
- Screenshot import flow (Claude Vision extracts addresses from Speed X screenshots)
- Live barcode scanning
- Zone assignment (currently count-based — being replaced)
- OSRM route optimization
- Leaflet map with zone color markers

### What is being replaced / added:
- COUNT-BASED zone balancing → REMOVED (this caused re-sorting chaos)
- Replacing with: K-MEANS GEOGRAPHIC CLUSTERING (zones based on address location, not count)
- Adding: ZIP code sector visualization (color-coded sectors on map)
- Adding: Address intelligence database (learns zones from route history)
- Adding: Loading plan screen (shown before physical sorting begins)

## Core Rules — DO NOT VIOLATE
1. Packages are touched ONCE — during loading. Never re-sorted.
2. Scanning phase = data collection only. No physical sorting signals during scan.
3. K-means runs ONCE after all packages are scanned and Optimize is hit.
4. Sectors are LOCKED after optimize. No rebalancing after that point.
5. Late additions → appended to end of route. No re-clustering.
6. Sector count = max 5 (matches vehicle zone count).
7. Loading plan screen must show before any sorting begins (which sector → which car zone).

## The Correct Flow
PHASE 1 — SCAN: Scan all packages. Dots appear on map (visual only). No sorting yet.
PHASE 2 — OPTIMIZE: K-means runs on complete dataset. Sectors finalized + locked.
           Route numbered 1→end. Loading plan generated.
PHASE 3 — SORT ONCE: Follow loading plan. One pass. Done.
PHASE 4 — DRIVE: Sequential route. No backtracking.

## Address Intelligence DB (In Progress)
- Every scanned/imported address saved with: ZIP, coordinates, sector assignment, route date
- Over time: ZIP → sector mapping is learned and predicted on scan
- Apartment complexes and recurring addresses auto-recognized
- Goal: by last scan, system semi-predicts full route

## Do Not Touch
- OSRM routing integration (working)
- Vehicle zone definitions (suv_midsize confirmed correct)
- Claude Vision address extraction logic

## Constants
- ZONE_LOCK_THRESHOLD = 20 (legacy — being phased out)
- ZONE_STABLE_MILES = 0.15mi
- Detroit ZIP codes are primary operating area (e.g. 48202 ~3.3mi → ~4 zones)

## Key Context
- This is a real production tool used daily by Speed X drivers
- Speed and reliability matter more than polish
- Director X uses this personally — UX must be frictionless
- No redundancy in workflow — every interaction must have a purpose
